      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis power-law model form must be justified against mechanistic RBC damage models; turbulence model selection must be validated for rotating blood-contacting geometries.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model is used without comparison to mechanistic alternatives. k-omega SST turbulence closure is selected based on general rotating machinery literature rather than blood pump-specific validation. Model form uncertainty is unquantified. Epistemic gap. Achieved level 1 against required level 5."
